# Moor a deep-sea trader alongside the quay: 25.4 m x 8.8 m.
# Kyrenia is the best-PRESERVED merchantman, not the biggest -- she was a coaster. The grain
# ships that fed Athens were far larger. Use these on the outer/deeper berths so the waterfront
# reads as a working port with a range of tonnage, not a car park of identical hulls.
# Deeper draught, so it sinks further than the coaster.
function trireme:moor_at {scale:"14.0",sink:"-6.0"}
